---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Worship — Friday: Repent"
  description="The 6 R's of Repentance and a 50-point inventory for self-examination for your Friday Repent practice."
>
  <div class="takeaways-content pg-page">
    <a href="/worship/takeaways-weekly-prayer-plan/" class="pg-back">← Back to Weekly Prayer Plan</a>

    <div class="pg-header">
      <div class="pg-day-badge">Friday · Repent</div>
      <h1 class="pg-title">The 6 R's of Repentance</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- THE 6 R's -->
    <div class="pg-six-r-stack">

      <div class="pg-r-card">
        <div class="pg-r-number">1</div>
        <div class="pg-r-body">
          <h2 class="pg-r-title">Recognize <span class="pg-r-sub">— Acknowledge Your Sin Before God</span></h2>
          <p class="pg-r-prayer">Lord, I recognize that I have sinned by <span class="pg-blank">_________________________________</span>. This has caused harm to myself and to <span class="pg-blank">_________________________________</span>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pg-r-card">
        <div class="pg-r-number">2</div>
        <div class="pg-r-body">
          <h2 class="pg-r-title">Repent <span class="pg-r-sub">— Turn Your Heart Toward the Father</span></h2>
          <p class="pg-r-prayer">Lord, I agree with You that <span class="pg-blank">______________</span> is sin and falls short of Your perfect design for my life. I choose to turn away from this sin and return to You.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pg-r-card">
        <div class="pg-r-number">3</div>
        <div class="pg-r-body">
          <h2 class="pg-r-title">Renounce <span class="pg-r-sub">— Break Every Unholy Connection</span></h2>
          <p class="pg-r-prayer">I renounce any spiritual bondage or evil influence that may have gained access through this sin. I reject this sin and any perceived benefits it offered, knowing they were deceptions that robbed me of Your best. I now choose to walk in Your ways alone.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pg-r-card">
        <div class="pg-r-number">4</div>
        <div class="pg-r-body">
          <h2 class="pg-r-title">Receive <span class="pg-r-sub">— Embrace God's Gift of Freedom</span></h2>
          <p class="pg-r-prayer">Lord, I humbly receive the forgiveness You freely offer through the cross. Please cleanse me completely and remove any barrier that would keep me from experiencing the fullness of Your forgiveness and grace.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pg-r-card">
        <div class="pg-r-number">5</div>
        <div class="pg-r-body">
          <h2 class="pg-r-title">Realign <span class="pg-r-sub">— Surrender to God's Perfect Will</span></h2>
          <p class="pg-r-prayer">Lord, I commit to seeking fulfillment only in ways that honor You. Please reveal the path to victory over this sin and show me the practical steps needed for lasting change. If I need accountability or support from others, make that clear to me. I trust that "I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me!"</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pg-r-card pg-r-card--praise">
        <div class="pg-r-number pg-r-number--praise">6</div>
        <div class="pg-r-body">
          <h2 class="pg-r-title">Rejoice <span class="pg-r-sub">— Celebrate Your Restoration in Christ</span></h2>
          <p class="pg-r-prayer">Lord Jesus, I overflow with gratitude and praise for Your transforming work in my life! Thank You for Your boundless love, complete forgiveness, true freedom, deep healing, and faithful provision.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div><!-- /.pg-six-r-stack -->

    <!-- INVENTORY FOR SELF-EXAMINATION -->
    <div class="pg-scripture-header">
      <h2 class="pg-scripture-title">Inventory for Self-Examination</h2>
      <p class="pg-scripture-sub">50 Areas to Consider</p>
    </div>

    <section class="pg-section">
      <h2 class="pg-section-label">Inward / Heart Sins</h2>
      <ol class="pg-list" start="1">
        <li>Pride disguised as confidence or "being right"</li>
        <li>Self-righteousness toward people who sin differently</li>
        <li>Spiritual apathy or lukewarm faith</li>
        <li>Loving comfort more than obedience</li>
        <li>Fear of people's opinions more than fear of God</li>
        <li>Envy fueled by social media comparison</li>
        <li>Bitterness that's been justified and nursed</li>
        <li>Unforgiveness hidden behind "boundaries"</li>
        <li>Anxiety rooted in control rather than trust</li>
        <li>Identity grounded more in roles or success than in Christ</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="pg-section pg-section--alt">
      <h2 class="pg-section-label">Sins of the Mind</h2>
      <ol class="pg-list" start="11">
        <li>Consuming content that slowly dulls holiness</li>
        <li>Pornography or sexual fantasy normalized by culture</li>
        <li>Entertaining resentment in private thoughts</li>
        <li>Obsessing over money, status, or security</li>
        <li>Judging others internally while appearing gracious outwardly</li>
        <li>Constant distraction that crowds out prayer</li>
        <li>Cynicism masquerading as wisdom</li>
        <li>Believing lies about God's character (He's distant, harsh, disappointed)</li>
        <li>Replaying offenses instead of surrendering them</li>
        <li>Daydreaming about escape rather than faithfulness</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="pg-section">
      <h2 class="pg-section-label">Speech &amp; Communication</h2>
      <ol class="pg-list" start="21">
        <li>Gossip labeled as "concern" or "venting"</li>
        <li>Sarcasm that wounds rather than builds</li>
        <li>Speaking truth without love</li>
        <li>Remaining silent when love requires speaking up</li>
        <li>Complaining as a default posture</li>
        <li>Exaggeration or half-truths for self-protection</li>
        <li>Public kindness with private cruelty</li>
        <li>Online speech that lacks grace or humility</li>
        <li>Using prayer language to sound spiritual rather than be sincere</li>
        <li>Talking more about God than to God</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="pg-section pg-section--alt">
      <h2 class="pg-section-label">Relationships &amp; Community</h2>
      <ol class="pg-list" start="31">
        <li>Avoiding reconciliation because it's uncomfortable</li>
        <li>Withholding grace while demanding it for ourselves</li>
        <li>Loving selectively — only those who are easy or like us</li>
        <li>Neglecting the poor, lonely, or marginalized</li>
        <li>Using people instead of serving them</li>
        <li>Staying in community superficially to avoid accountability</li>
        <li>Refusing to admit wrong or ask forgiveness</li>
        <li>Harboring superiority toward unbelievers</li>
        <li>Parenting (or leading) through control rather than love</li>
        <li>Neglecting marriage or family for lesser priorities</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="pg-section">
      <h2 class="pg-section-label">Faith &amp; Practice</h2>
      <ol class="pg-list" start="41">
        <li>Treating church as a service to consume, not a body to belong to</li>
        <li>Praying only in crisis</li>
        <li>Reading Scripture for information, not transformation</li>
        <li>Trusting political ideologies more than the kingdom of God</li>
        <li>Selective obedience — following God where it's convenient</li>
        <li>Hoarding time, money, or gifts instead of stewarding them</li>
        <li>Excusing sin by calling it "personality"</li>
        <li>Resisting the Holy Spirit's conviction</li>
        <li>Forgetting gratitude and living entitled</li>
        <li>Failing to love God with heart, soul, mind, and strength</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <blockquote class="pg-closing-quote">
      "Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me."
      <cite>— Psalm 51:10</cite>
    </blockquote>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Page wrapper ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.pg-page {
  max-width: 860px;
  padding-top: 1.5rem;
}

/* ── Back link ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.pg-back {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: #9a8e82;
  text-decoration: none;
  margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  transition: color 0.15s;
}
.pg-back:hover { color: #b79c5c; }

/* ── Header ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.pg-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.pg-day-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
